choices.text:
Sally has 3 brothers. Her brothers have 2 sisters. How many sisters does Sally have?
Based on the information given, we can deduce that each brother has one sister and two brothers-in-law (i.e., sisters' husbands). Therefore, Sally would have half of that, which is 1 brother-in-law or 0.5 siblings. So, Sally does not have any sisters.
